Stated simply: more information/education and less entertainment.
No more hedge fund activists talking their books and feathering their own nests.
No more self confident (but shallow) statements from talking heads who have undistinguished careers but are presented as stars.
No more talking heads emphasizing their winners and neglecting/sweeping under the carpet their losers.
No more floor traders talking economics, no more strategists talking trading, no more count down clocks for the most inane events.
No more breathless narratives, no more commentary from so called experts who's information bases are 3 miles wide and only inches deep.
One biz network would reduce the fluff and meaningless banter. And bring value added commentary.
I think we would all be better off with only one business network - there is just so much BS and little value added.
